title: Naru Shinoya
text:
is a Japanese <a href="badminton">badminton</a> player.
Achievements.
BWF World Championships.
"Mixed doubles"
BWF World Tour (2 runners-up).
The BWF World Tour, announced on 19 March 2017 and implemented in 2018, is a series of elite badminton tournaments, sanctioned by <a href="Badminton%20World%20Federation">Badminton World Federation</a> (BWF). The BWF World Tour are divided into six levels, namely World Tour Finals, Super 1000, Super 750, Super 500, Super 300 (part of the HSBC World Tour), and the BWF Tour Super 100.
"Women's doubles"
"Mixed doubles"
BWF Grand Prix (3 runners-up).
The BWF Grand Prix has two levels, the <a href="BWF%20Grand%20Prix%20and%20Grand%20Prix%20Gold">Grand Prix and Grand Prix Gold</a>. It is a series of badminton tournaments, sanctioned by <a href="Badminton%20World%20Federation">Badminton World Federation</a> (BWF) since 2007.
"Women's doubles"
BWF International Challenge/Series (7 titles, 5 runners-up).
